                            ],
                            "spans": [
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1269,
                                        689,
                                        2319,
                                        1184
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "In the HALy.ID project, alongside a comprehensive analysis of RGB images primarily captured by UAVs, we also conducted an assessment of spectral imaging as a potential method for field monitoring to detect the presence of BMSB. To this purpose, SWIR- HSI and Vis- NIR MSI systems were evaluated both in the laboratory and in the field, respectively. In fact, unlike cameras operating exclusively within the visible spectrum, they may mitigate misclassifications caused by BMSB's resemblance to vegetal backgrounds with similar colors, such as bark or brown leaves."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
                    "index": 7
                },
                {
